Moody's Investors Service Inc said itdowngraded 700 mln dlrs of debt of Dana Corp and its unit DanaCredit Corp.    Cut were the parent's senior debt and industrial revenuebonds to A-3 from A-2. Moody's reduced to Prime-2 from Prime-1the commercial paper of Dana and its credit unit.    Moody's cited deterioration in capital structure and debtprotection measurements due to aggressive balance sheetmanagement.  Moreover, Dana's financial leverage rose to43 pct from 22 pct in 1984 and may climb even more aftercompleting its ongoing stock repurchase program, Moody's said. Reuter&#3;